{#- CREDENTIALS -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qbps-credentials" style="padding-top:24px;">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:8px;">Certified by Intuit &middot; Payroll, Online (L2), Desktop, Enterprise</div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor credentials</h2>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for s in credStats %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ s.value }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ s.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <ul class="checklist">
      {%- for c in credentials %}<li>{{ c | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

{#- DEFINITION -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbps-definition" style="padding-top:24px;background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:8px;">In plain terms</div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">QuickBooks Payroll setup, plainly.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in definition %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- SCOPE -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbps-scope" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">What setup actually includes</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Eight categories of work, every engagement.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 24px;max-width:70ch;">Every category below is part of standard payroll setup. Skip any one and you create downstream problems &mdash; sometimes immediate, sometimes surfacing at year-end. The full scope is what proper setup means.</p>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for s in scope %}
      <div class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ s.num }}</span><h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ s.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- PRICING -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qbps-pricing">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Pricing</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Fixed-fee setup, scoped by complexity.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 24px;max-width:70ch;">Pricing reflects engagement complexity, not hours. Every setup engagement gets a written scope before any work begins &mdash; assessed during the complimentary discovery call.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for t in pricing %}
      <div class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ t.eyebrow | safe }}</span><h3>{{ t.tier | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 8px;"><strong>{{ t.cadence | safe }}.</strong> {{ t.fit | safe }}</p><ul class="checklist">{% for inc in t.includes %}<li>{{ inc | safe }}</li>{% endfor %}</ul><p style="margin:12px 0 0;"><a href="/contact/?intent=qb-payroll-setup">Book the discovery call <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a></p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:18px 0 0;max-width:70ch;">{{ pricingNote | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{#- ERRORS -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbps-errors" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Why proper setup matters</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Setup errors compound for years.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 24px;max-width:70ch;">Payroll setup mistakes aren&rsquo;t recoverable through quarterly corrections &mdash; they require restate-and-refile work. The cost of fixing later is typically meaningfully higher than the cost of proper initial setup.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for e in errors %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ e.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ e.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- TIMING -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qbps-timing">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">When to set up payroll</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">January 1 is materially simpler than mid-year.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 24px;max-width:70ch;">Setup timing changes both scope and pricing. Three patterns worth understanding before booking:</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for t in timing %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ t.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ t.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- ROUTING -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbps-routing" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">One question before setup</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Are you sure QuickBooks Payroll is the right provider?</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 24px;max-width:70ch;">Setup engagements assume the provider decision is made. If you&rsquo;re still evaluating, that decision should happen <em>before</em> setup &mdash; switching providers after setup creates the mid-year-transition friction described above. Three paths:</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for b in routing %}
      <a class="dc-card hub-card" href="{{ b.href }}"><h3>{{ b.opener | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ b.body | safe }}</p><span class="hub-card__go">{{ b.cta | safe }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span></a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- OPERATOR -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qbps-operator">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:8px;">Who performs the work</div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">Certified Payroll ProAdvisor. Fixed-fee. No commission.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in operatorCopy %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- RELATED -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qbps-related">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:8px;">Related references</div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">Other payroll resources.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for n in related %}
      <h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.title | safe }}</a></h3>
      <p>{{ n.body | safe }}</p>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
